      • successfulTransactionToken

        void successfulTransactionToken(TransactionToken transactionToken)
        This method will be called when a card has been successfully read and translated to a Clearent Transaction Token. This token can be used later to perform a payment.
        Parameters:
        transactionToken - contains the token (TransactionToken.transactionToken) and associated metadata.

      • lcdDisplay

        void lcdDisplay(int mode,
                String[] lines,
                int timeout)
        lcdDisplay - This method sends back information about the process.
        Parameters:
        mode - LCD Display Mode: 0x01: Menu Display. A selection must be made to resume the transaction 0x02: Normal Display get function key. A function must be selected to resume the transaction 0x03: Display without input. Message is displayed without pausing the transaction 0x04: List of languages are presented for selection. A selection must be made to resume the transaction 0x10: Clear Screen. Command to clear the LCD screen
        lines - Line(s) of data to display
        timeout - Timeout value when displaying dialog box

      • lcdDisplay

        void lcdDisplay(int mode,
                String[] lines,
                int timeout,
                byte[] languageCode,
                byte messageId)
        lcdDisplay - This method sends back information that can be used to prompt the user for an answer.
        Parameters:
        mode - LCD Display Mode: 0x01: Menu Display. A selection must be made to resume the transaction 0x02: Normal Display get function key. A function must be selected to resume the transaction 0x03: Display without input. Message is displayed without pausing the transaction 0x04: List of languages are presented for selection. A selection must be made to resume the transaction 0x10: Clear Screen. Command to clear the LCD screen
        lines - Line(s) of data to display
        timeout - Timeout value when displaying dialog box
        languageCode - 2 bytes language code ("EN", "ES", "FR", or "ZH") of the LCD message.
        messageId - 1 byte id (from 1 to 34) for a LCD message string.

      • timeout

        void timeout(int errorCode)
        Notify the plug status of phone jack. Timeout when wait for the response. This happens in the process of get PINpad, swipe MSR, EMV Level 2 transaction
        Parameters:
        errorCode - error code

      • LoadXMLConfigFailureInfo

        void LoadXMLConfigFailureInfo(int index,
                              String message)
        Alerts when the xml configuration failed to load
        Parameters:
        index - 1: "This phone model is not supported by the current SDK. Please contact supporter for assistance."; 2: "Wrong XML file name, please set the filename or enable the auto update."; 3: "The XML file does not exist and the auto update disabled."; 4: "Can't download the XML file. Please make sure the network is accessible.";
        message - message information when loading the XML file.

      • msgToConnectDevice

        void msgToConnectDevice()
        Notifies the framework is in the process of connecting the device. When connecting for the first time the card reader will have EMV configuration applied.
